of this study shocked the research community and a report about it went viral. Click on the link below to read the open-access article \"Gene name errors: Lessons not learnt\" by @abeysooriyaGeneNameErrors2021 to find out whether the situation has improved since 2016 and answer the questions below.\n\n> Abeysooriya, Mandhri, Megan Soria, Mary Sravya Kasu & Mark Ziemann. 2021. Gene name errors: Lessons not learned. PLOS Computational Biology. Public Library of Science 17(7). e1008984. <https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1008984>.\n\n[**Q2.12**]{style=\"color:green;\"} Has the proportion of genetics publications with Excel gene lists affected by auto-formatting errors decreased since 2016?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q2_12\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q2_12()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q2_12\" id=\"answer_Q2_12_1\" value=\"No, it has remained stable.\"/>\nNo, it has remained stable.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q2_12\" id=\"answer_Q2_12_2\" value=\"Yes, it decreased between 2016 and 2020.\"/>\nYes, it decreased between 2016 and 2020.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q2_12\" id=\"answer_Q2_12_3\" value=\"No, it increased between 2016 and 2020.\"/>\nNo, it increased between 2016 and 2020.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q2_12\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q2_12() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q2_12']['answer_Q2_12'].value;if (x == 'No, it has remained stable.'){text = 'ThatŌĆÖs right: Even though the first widely-read report about this was published in 2016, it was just as bad a problem in 2020!';} else {text = 'No. Take another look at Fig. 1C from the paper.';} document.getElementById('result_Q2_12').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementBy